<worksheet xmlns="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/spreadsheetml/2006/main"><sheetPr><outlinePr summaryBelow="1" summaryRight="1"/><pageSetUpPr/></sheetPr><dimension ref="A1:B23"/><sheetViews><sheetView workbookViewId="0"><pane ySplit="1" topLeftCell="A2" activePane="bottomLeft" state="frozen"/><selection pane="bottomLeft" activeCell="A1" sqref="A1"/></sheetView></sheetViews><sheetFormatPr baseColWidth="8" defaultRowHeight="15"/><cols><col width="22" customWidth="1" min="1" max="1"/><col width="70" customWidth="1" min="2" max="2"/></cols><sheetData><row r="1" ht="32" customHeight="1"><c r="A1" s="1" t="inlineStr"><is><t>How to Fill the Contacts Import Template</t></is></c></row><row r="2" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A2" s="10" t="inlineStr"><is><t>COLUMN</t></is></c><c r="B2" s="11" t="inlineStr"><is><t>WHAT TO ENTER</t></is></c></row><row r="3" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A3" s="12" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Contact Name &#9733;</t></is></c><c r="B3" s="13" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Full name of the person or company. Example: "Ahmed Traders" or "Muhammad Ali Sb"</t></is></c></row><row r="4" ht="56" customHeight="1"><c r="A4" s="12" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Contact Type &#9733;</t></is></c><c r="B4" s="13" t="inlineStr"><is><t>"Customer" = someone who buys from you (they pay you).
"Supplier" = someone you buy from (you pay them).
Use the dropdown &#8212; do not type anything else.</t></is></c></row><row r="5" ht="56" customHeight="1"><c r="A5" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Opening Balance</t></is></c><c r="B5" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>The amount of money already owed BEFORE you start using the system.
If there is no existing debt, leave this blank or enter 0.
Enter numbers only &#8212; no Rs, no commas. Example: 15000 not Rs 15,000</t></is></c></row><row r="6" ht="104" customHeight="1"><c r="A6" s="16" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Balance Direction &#9733;</t></is></c><c r="B6" s="17" t="inlineStr"><is><t>This tells the system WHO owes WHO:

&#9989; To Receive &#8594; The contact owes YOU money (e.g. a customer who still has an unpaid bill)
&#9989; To Pay &#8594; YOU owe the contact money (e.g. a supplier you have not paid yet)

Leave BLANK if Opening Balance is 0 or empty.</t></is></c></row><row r="7" ht="40" customHeight="1"><c r="A7" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Phone Number</t></is></c><c r="B7" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Mobile or landline. Example: +923001234567
Optional &#8212; can be left blank.</t></is></c></row><row r="8" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A8" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Email</t></is></c><c r="B8" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Email address. Optional.</t></is></c></row><row r="9" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A9" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Address</t></is></c><c r="B9" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>City, area, or full address. Optional.</t></is></c></row><row r="10" ht="40" customHeight="1"><c r="A10" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Credit Limit</t></is></c><c r="B10" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Maximum amount this contact is allowed to owe you at one time.
Leave blank for no limit. Numbers only.</t></is></c></row><row r="11" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A11" s="14" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Notes</t></is></c><c r="B11" s="15" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Any extra information. Optional.</t></is></c></row><row r="12" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A12" s="18" t="inlineStr"></c><c r="B12" s="18" t="inlineStr"></c></row><row r="13" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A13" s="19" t="inlineStr"><is><t>&#9888;&#65039;  COMMON MISTAKES</t></is></c><c r="B13" s="20" t="inlineStr"></c></row><row r="14" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A14" s="21" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Wrong Type</t></is></c><c r="B14" s="22" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Do NOT write "client" or "vendor" &#8212; only "Customer" or "Supplier" are accepted.</t></is></c></row><row r="15" ht="40" customHeight="1"><c r="A15" s="21" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Balance without Direction</t></is></c><c r="B15" s="22" t="inlineStr"><is><t>If you enter an Opening Balance, you MUST also select a Balance Direction.
Without a direction the system does not know whether to record it as money owed to you or by you.</t></is></c></row><row r="16" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A16" s="21" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Rs symbol in balance</t></is></c><c r="B16" s="22" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Enter 5000 not "Rs 5,000". The Rs symbol and commas will cause an error.</t></is></c></row><row r="17" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A17" s="21" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Both customer and supplier</t></is></c><c r="B17" s="22" t="inlineStr"><is><t>If the same person is both a customer and a supplier, create two separate rows &#8212; one as Customer, one as Supplier.</t></is></c></row><row r="18" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A18" s="18" t="inlineStr"></c><c r="B18" s="18" t="inlineStr"></c></row><row r="19" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A19" s="23" t="inlineStr"><is><t>&#9989;  QUICK RULES</t></is></c><c r="B19" s="24" t="inlineStr"></c></row><row r="20" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A20" s="23" t="inlineStr"><is><t>&#9733; = Required</t></is></c><c r="B20" s="24" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Contact Name, Contact Type, and Balance Direction (when balance &gt; 0) are required.</t></is></c></row><row r="21" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A21" s="23" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Dropdowns</t></is></c><c r="B21" s="24" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Contact Type and Balance Direction have dropdowns. Click the cell and use the arrow to select.</t></is></c></row><row r="22" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A22" s="23" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Example rows</t></is></c><c r="B22" s="24" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Rows 5&#8211;9 on the Import sheet are examples. Delete them before importing.</t></is></c></row><row r="23" ht="24" customHeight="1"><c r="A23" s="23" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Re-running</t></is></c><c r="B23" s="24" t="inlineStr"><is><t>Safe to re-import &#8212; the system skips duplicate names.</t></is></c></row></sheetData><mergeCells count="1"><mergeCell ref="A1:B1"/></mergeCells><pageMargins left="0.75" right="0.75" top="1" bottom="1" header="0.5" footer="0.5"/></worksheet>